            <thetext>In an application, *all* framework resources are copied (like 
.../framework/source/resource/*) through &#39;build-resources&#39;, although they are 
not required by the application.

It appears that a library name space like &#39;foo&#39; and an asset require like 
&#39;foo/*&#39; would make the resource filter match everything if &#39;foo&#39; also appears 
as a path component leading to the framework: 
&quot;..../foo/.../framework/source/resource/...&quot;. This defies resource filtering 
according to #asset specs.</thetext>
